      "sc:citation": {
        "@id": "https://doi.org/10.18129/B9.bioc.discordant"
      },
      "sc:description": "Discordant is an R package that identifies pairs of features that correlate differently between phenotypic groups, with application to -omics data sets. Discordant uses a mixture model that “bins” molecular feature pairs based on their type of coexpression or coabbundance. Algorithm is explained further in \"Differential Correlation for Sequencing Data\"\" (Siska et al. 2016).",
